## Exercise 4: SSH Remote Access

**Goal:** Connect remotely from Kali to Ubuntu using SSH.

### Step 1: Connect via SSH
```bash
ssh ronit@192.168.115.129
```

### Step 2: Accept Host Key (first time only)
```
The authenticity of host '192.168.115.129' can't be established.
Are you sure you want to continue connecting (yes/no)? yes
```

### Step 3: Enter Password
Type the Ubuntu account password (no characters will display).

### Result
Once authenticated, the Kali terminal connects directly to the Ubuntu shell — demonstrating how SSH (port 22) provides full remote command-line access.

